BENIN – The newly elected chair­man of the Edo State chapter of All Farm­ers Association of Nigeria (AFAN), Alhaji Bako E. Dogwo, has called on Nigeri­an farmers to be up and doing, reminding them that a nation without adequate food is doom. Dogwo, who made the call in his post-election speech, also called on government at all levels to make adequate provision in their budgets to enhance the productivity of the Nigerian farmers. According to him, a country that cannot feed its populace is a failed nation and assured his members of good time ahead. He appealed to all farmers in the state to join the associ­ation, just as he assured them that the welfare of members would be the priority of the union. He also told them that all members of the union would be given equal opportunity to excel, as no one would be dis­criminated against. At the keenly contested election, which took place in Benin City, His Royal High­ness, Alhaji Bako Dogwo, was elected chairman, while Mrs Gladys Iyore Emuze and Alhaji Zinat Shaka, got the position of Secretary and treasurer, respectively. Also elected member of the excutive is the Deputy State Chairman, Chief A.O. Osayande. Others are the three vice chairmen representing the three Senatorial districts of the state, Alhaji Aminu Yakubu, Mr. Felix Oiseo­moje, North; Chief Francis Olaye, South and Arugboba Sylvester Ebhodaghe, Cen­tral.